Definition: a scale formerly used to describe the magnitude of an earthquake
Example: an earthquake detected only by seismographs is a I and an earthquake that destroys all buildings is a XII
Synonyms: scale, noun, cognition, geology, c, a, formerly, used, to, describe, the, magnitude, of, an, earthquake, detected, only, by, seismographs, is, I, and, that, destroys, all, buildings, XII
Category: noun.relation
